<HEADLINE>
<P>
SATELLITE TV 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The most recent honeymoon of the Europeans with satellite television (Part I, 
Feb.8) includes an experience that escaped your London correspondent: the first 
24-hour-a-day satellite channel in Spanish in Europe known as Galavision. It is 
a mixture of news and information services called ECO. It is actually a new 
opportunity for the dial of the Spanish-speaking people in Western Europe. 
</P>
<P>
FELIX CORTES 
</P>
<P>
Executive Vice President 
</P>
<P>
ECO 
</P>
<P>
Los Angeles 
</P>
</TEXT>
