<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE BASKETBALL ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
NEW ORLEANS UPSETS SLUMPING FLORIDA ST. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The New Orleans men's basketball team hadn't defeated a ranked team in 14 years 
of National Collegiate Athletic Assn. Division I competition. 
</P>
<P>
That changed Tuesday night, however, with an 83-77 victory over struggling 
12th-ranked Florida State at New Orleans. 
</P>
<P>
Robert Hokett made three three-point shots in the final eight minutes and Tony 
Harris made four free throws in the final 40 seconds as New Orleans handed 
Florida State (19-5) its third consecutive defeat. 
</P>
<P>
New Orleans (16-9) took a 60-55 lead on Hokett's first three-pointer, but 
Florida State tied the score, 62-62, on Aubry Boyd's two free throws with 5:41 
left. 
</P>
<P>
Hokett made his second three-point basket with 5:30 left. Florida State tied 
the score, 67-67, on Derrick Mitchell's free throws with 3:43 left. Hokett then 
made his third three-pointer, giving New Orleans the lead for good, 70-67, with 
3:27 remaining. 
</P>
<P>
North Carolina 109, Nevada-Reno 86 -- Kevin Madden scored 21 points and J.R. 
Reid and Rick Fox added 19 each as the No. 5 Tar Heels (23-5) got their fifth 
consecutive victory in the nonconference game at Chapel Hill, N.C. 
</P>
<P>
Nevada Reno (14-10) took a 12-3 lead three minutes into the game, but North 
Carolina tied the score, 17-17, and took the lead for good when Fox, who scored 
15 points in the first half, made two free throws with 13:04 remaining. 
</P>
<P>
Seton Hall 63, St. John's 60 -- John Morton scored all 22 of his points in the 
second half and Andrew Gaze's two free throws with 2:17 left broke the final 
tie as No. 15 Seton Hall won the Big East Conference game at East Rutherford, 
N.J. 
</P>
<P>
Jayson Williams scored 25 points for St. John's (14-10, 5-8). 
</P>
<P>
Neither team led by more than five points in the second half. There were five 
lead changes and six ties, the last at 58 when Williams scored on a drive with 
2:26 remaining. 
</P>
<P>
Notre Dame 83, Dayton 66 -- Keith Robinson scored 25 points -- his fifth 
consecutive game of scoring more than 20 -- and had 16 rebounds to lead the 
Irish at Dayton, Ohio. 
</P>
<P>
Joe Fredrick added 20 for the Irish (17-5) and Keith Tower had 13 and Jamere 
Jackson 12. 
</P>
<P>
Montana St. 82, Creighton 80 -- Senior center Mike Fellows scored 14 points, 
including the decisive three late in the game, to help lift Bobcats to a 
nonconference victory at Bozeman, Mont. 
</P>
<P>
Fellows scored and was fouled with 2:32 remaining. When he made the free throw, 
he put Montana State ahead, 82-76. 
</P>
<P>
Alabama-Birmingham 87, South Florida 59 -- Larry Rembert scored 25 points to 
lead Alabama-Birmingham to a Sun Belt Conference victory at Birmingham. 
</P>
</TEXT>
