<HEADLINE>
<P>
ALEMANY'S ROSSELLI BREAKS HAND IN A FALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Alemany High left-hander Joey Rosselli suffered a broken bone in his pitching 
hand in a fall at his home Monday night and will be sidelined at least six 
weeks. 
</P>
<P>
Rosselli, Alemany's starting quarterback this season, said that the hand will 
be placed in a cast for three to four weeks after he undergoes surgery 
Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
Rosselli compiled a 2-3 record as a sophomore last season with a 3.65 
earned-run average. He also batted .357 in 28 at-bats. 
</P>
