</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jesse Jackson made an appeal Monday for the "earliest possible" parole of soul 
singer James Brown, saying Brown had been a model prisoner and an inspiration 
to others. Jackson, who met with Brown for more than 90 minutes at the State 
Park Correctional Institute near Columbia, S.C., told USA Today that Brown's 
