BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
T-Bill Auction: The Treasury Department sold $7.2 billion of three-month bills 
at an average discount rate of 8.51%, up from 8.49% last week. Another $7.2 
billion of new six-month bills was sold at an average discount rate of 8.50%, 
down from 8.54% last week. The rates for six-month bills were the lowest since 
Jan. 30, when they averaged 8.39%. The rates for three-month bills were the 
highest since they averaged 8.57% on Feb. 6. The discount rate reflects the 
price discount received when government securities are purchased at less than 
face value. 
