<HEADLINE>
<P>
BUSH NAMES SPECIAL AIDE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
WASHINGTON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
President Bush on Tuesday announced the appointment of Shirley Green, who was 
his deputy press secretary when he was vice president, as his special assistant 
for presidential messages and correspondence. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Appointment; Wire 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA022289-0065 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 21781 </DOCID>
<DATE>
<P>
February 22, 1989, Wednesday, Home Edition 
</P>
</DATE>
<SECTION>
<P>
