<HEADLINE>
<P>
OHYAMA REPLACES KNUSSEN FOR PHILHARMONIC CONCERTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Los Angeles Philharmonic assistant conductor Heiichiro Ohyama will replace 
Oliver Knussen in concerts with the orchestra, Thursday, Friday and Sunday at 
the Dorothy Chandler Pavilion and Saturday at the Bob Hope Cultural Center in 
Palm Desert. The British composer/conductor is ill and will not be able to fly 
in from England. The program for all concerts now lists Mussorgsky's Prelude to 
"Khovanshchina," Shostakovich's Second Cello Concerto, with Natasha Gutman, 
Carter's Elegy and Stravinsky's "Firebird" Suite (1945). 
</P>
</TEXT>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
