<HEADLINE>
<P>
'MAESTRO' PHOTOGRAPHS ON DISPLAY IN GRAND HALL OF MUSIC CENTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"Maestro," an exhibit of photographic portraits of internationally renowned 
conductors by Tom Zimberoff, is on display in the Grand Hall of the Music 
Center through May 7. 
</P>
<P>
Zimberoff, formerly a classical music student at USC, covered violinist Jascha 
Heifetz's farewell recital for Time magazine in 1972 and has since won acclaim 
for his political, publicity and entertainment photography. 
</P>
<P>
The exhibit's 20 portraits, including those of Erich Leinsdorf, Zubin Mehta, 
Andre Previn, Simon Rattle and Michael Tilson Thomas, were selected from more 
than 50 of Zimberoff's works photographed over the last eight years portraying 
almost all of the world's principal orchestra conductors. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
