<HEADLINE>
<P>
CINEMATOGRAPHERS GROUP SETS AWARD NOMINATIONS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The American Society of Cinematographers has selected nominees for the third 
annual ASC Awards to be given March 5 at the Beverly Hilton. 
</P>
<P>
In the theatrical features category, the nominees are Peter Biziou 
("Mississippi Burning"), Conrad Hall ("Tequila Sunrise"), Sven Nykvist ("The 
Unbearable Lightness of Being"), Philippe Rousselot ("Dangerous Liaisons") and 
John Seale ("Rain Man"). 
</P>
<P>
Nominated for TV miniseries: Dietrich Lohmann ("War and Remembrance"), 
Cristiano Pogany ("Noble House"),Wolfgang Treu ("Hemingway") and William Wages 
("Gore Vidal's Lincoln"). 
</P>
<P>
Other categories cover episodic series and specials and pilots. Veteran 
cinematographer Joe Biroc will receive the group's Lifetime Achievement Award 
for a career that has spanned seven decades, from silent films to television. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<SUBJECT>
<P>
