<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY DIGEST: LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF; 
</P>
<P>
EL TORO; 
</P>
<P>
SUSPECT HELD IN SLAYING OF MAN FOUND AT MOTEL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 21-year-old Riverside man has been arrested on suspicion of homicide in the 
death of Lee Matthew Clyde, 20, whose body was found in an El Toro motel room 
Monday. 
</P>
<P>
Gregory Romano Benjamin was arrested at an El Toro apartment complex Monday 
night after information developed by investigators "pointed to this person," 
said Lt. Robert Rivas of the county Sheriff's Department. 
</P>
<P>
Rivas said he had no information on a motive in the killing or the relationship 
between Benjamin and the victim. 
</P>
<P>
Clyde, who suffered a trauma to the head, was found at 9 a.m. Monday in a room 
in the Quality Suites Inn in the 2300 block of Lake Center Drive. Coroner's 
officials refused to provide the findings of an autopsy conducted Tuesday 
afternoon. 
</P>
<P>
Rivas said he did not know if or when Clyde, who lived in El Toro, or Benjamin 
had rented the motel room. No further information was available Tuesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
