COMMUNITY COLLEGE ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
FULLERTON POWERS PAST CERRITOS FOR 9-2 VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Fullerton College used three home runs to defeat Cerritos, 9-2, in a 
nonconference baseball game at Fullerton Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
John Mele, a sophomore catcher, hit a two-run home run during a four-run first 
for Fullerton (4-6). Russ Barnes had three hits, including a solo home run, and 
Mike Segovia also hit a solo homer for Fullerton. 
</P>
<P>
Cerritos falls to 10-2 with the loss. 
</P>
<P>
Mark Rogers (1-1) pitched 3 1/3 scoreless innings in relief for the victory. He 
struck out three and allowed two hits. Trevor Painton pitched the final three 
innings for his first save. 
</P>
<P>
In other nonconference games: 
</P>
<P>
Golden West 12, Los Angeles Harbor 9 -- Robb Carabba had two doubles, a triple 
and three RBIs to lead Golden West (5-3) at home. Dave Westman had two hits, 
including a double, and three RBIs and Dan Villegas had two hits and an RBI 
also for Golden West, which had 13 hits. 
</P>
<P>
Toby Foreman pitched 8 2/3 innings to get the victory. 
</P>
<P>
Southwestern 6, Rancho Santiago 4 -- Southwestern scored two runs off Willie 
Navarrette in the top of the ninth to break a 4-4 tie. It was the first college 
loss for Navarrette, a sophomore left-hander, who was 11-0 last season. 
Navarrette (1-1) walked six batters, and three scored. Rancho Santiago (6-5) 
tied the score, 4-4, on a solo home run by John McTaggart in the fifth. Ed 
Renteria had two doubles and a single for Rancho Santiago. 
</P>
<P>
Cypress 6, Arizona State JV 2 -- Jason Friedman had three hits and three RBIs 
and Mike Neal had two hits and two RBIs for visiting Cypress (11-4). Ron Brown 
pitched the first five innings for the victory. 
</P>
<P>
Saddleback 6, El Camino 3 -- Matt Dahlgren hit a three-run home run for host 
Saddleback (5-1). 
</P>
<P>
In nonconference women's softball: 
</P>
<P>
Rancho Santiago College 4, Citrus 3 -- Rancho Santiago scored runs in the 
bottom of the seventh at home. The Dons (5-2) loaded the bases with two outs 
and Natalie Sanchez and LaTania Trotter walked to force in the winning run. 
</P>
<P>
Cypress 7, College of the Desert 0 -- Colleen Moore allowed only a hit in the 
first four innings for host Cypress. Alisha Bokano had three hits and scored 
two runs and Rose Ferrante and Karen Kuypers had two RBIs each for Cypress. 
</P>
<P>
Orange Coast 1, College of the Canyons 0 -- Sindy Rice reached second on a 
throwing error, went to third on a single by Kellie Newcombe and scored on a 
wild pitch in the sixth inning for host Orange Coast (5-2). 
</P>
<P>
In nonconference men's tennis: 
</P>
<P>
Cypress 8, Pasadena 1 -- Eric Glade won at No. 1 singles, 6-1, 6-1, and 
combined with Moses Kim to win at No. 1 doubles, 6-2, 6-2, for host Cypress 
(3-0). 
</P>
<P>
Rancho Santiago 8, Citrus 1 -- Omar Sary won at No. singles, 6-1, 7-6, and Alex 
Venidis won at No. 3 singles, 6-0, 6-0, for host Rancho Santiago. 
</P>
