<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE COLLEGES; 
</P>
<P>
GSAC BASKETBALL ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
BICKMORE RALLIES SCC WITH SECOND-HALF RUN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By PAMELA CEREN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Jeff Bickmore led Southern California College to a 79-67 victory over Fresno 
Pacific in a Golden State Athletic Conference basketball game Tuesday at SCC. 
</P>
<P>
SCC trailed at halftime, 32-27, but Bickmore scored 14 points during an 18-0 
SCC run in the second half. 
</P>
<P>
"We were pretty much standing around defensively, playing pretty flat-footed 
and passively," SCC Coach Bill Reynolds said. "And you could say we alluded to 
that rather strongly at halftime." 
</P>
<P>
Bickmore scored on a layup, then Terry Scruggs stole the ball and took it 
fullcourt for a layup. In the next 5 minutes SCC (25-3 overall, 12-3 in 
conference) used a full-court press to force eight bad Fresno shots. 
</P>
<P>
"The second half I was just getting the ball and getting good position inside," 
Bickmore said. "(The run) was caused mainly by our defense getting loose balls 
and making steals." 
</P>
<P>
Said Reynolds: "We usually get a spurt like that, thank goodness. And we never 
know if or when it will come." 
</P>
<P>
SCC shot 50% during the second half and 41% for the game, but a 13-point lead 
became six points, 67-61, with 4 minutes to play. 
</P>
<P>
"We had our peak and then went right back into the valley, " Reynolds said. "I 
guess that's really what you call game slippage." 
</P>
<P>
SCC and Fresno traded baskets the first 5 minutes of play and after tying the 
score, 14-14, and three scoreless minutes, Fresno (17-12, 8-5) pulled ahead to 
take the halftime lead. 
</P>
<P>
Bickmore led all scorers with 25 points, Scruggs added 22 and Todd Dixon had 
21. For Fresno, Donnie Johnson had 18, and Brian Falls had 11. 
</P>
<P>
In another Golden State Athletic Conference men's game: 
</P>
<P>
Cal Lutheran 130, Christ College Irvine 96 -- Steve deLaveaga scored a 
single-game school record 51 points for host Cal Lutheran. He was 20 of 30 from 
field and 7 of 12 from three-point range. It was the 81st consecutive game he 
has scored in double figures. He is averaging a conference high 28.1 points a 
game. 
</P>
<P>
Aaron Clasen scored 22 points and Albert Gay added 20 points and a team-high 10 
rebounds for Christ College (4-25, 0-13). 
</P>
<P>
In a Golden State Athletic Conference women's game: 
</P>
<P>
Fresno Pacific 66, Southern California 50 -- Irene Robles and Kellie Fry scored 
17 points each to lead visiting Fresno Pacific (21-7, 11-2). Roxanne Trost 
scored 12 and Paula Hale 11 for SCC (5-24, 1-11). 
</P>
</TEXT>
